WOLFSON'S RANKED IN U.S. NEWS SPECIALTIES

Wolfson Children's Hospital has been ranked in five of 10 specialties in U.S.
News & World Report's 2013-14 Best Children's Hospitals rankings.

Wolfson Children's Hospital ranked among the top 50 in diabetes & endocrinology;
neonatology; orthopedics; pulmonology; and urology. Wolfson previously had been
ranked in the top 50 in three categories. The top 50 designations for
neonatology and orthopedics are new.

U.S. News introduced the Best Children's Hospitals rankings in 2007. Rankings
may be viewed online at health.usnews.com/best-hospitals/pediatric-rankings and
will be published in the U.S. News Best Hospitals 2014 guidebook, available
beginning in August.

ST. VINCENT'S WINS AD CAMPAIGN AWARD

St. Vincent's HealthCare's "Above. Beyond. Because." advertising campaign has
been named the winner of an Aster Award, which recognizes excellence in health
care advertising.

The St. Vincent's campaign, which included TV and radio spots, billboards, print
ads and Internet videos, was one of eight selected a "Judges Choice" winner from
about 3,000 entries.

PEDIATRIC SOCIETY ANNOUNCES AWARDS

The Northeast Florida Pediatric Society has announced its annual awards.

Florida Sen. Stephen R. Wise was given the "Pediatric Advocate" award.
Pediatrician Kenneth Horn of Baptist Pediatrics was named "Pediatrician of the
Year." Pediatric urologist Mark A. Barrazza of Nemours Children's Clinic was
selected "Pediatric Surgical Subspecialist of the Year."

Pediatric anesthesiologist Robert B. Bryskin, of Nemours Children's Clinic was
named "Pediatric Innovator of the Year." Neonatologist Mary O. Lim of the
University of Florida College of Medicine-Jacksonville was named "Pediatric
Medical Subspecialist of the Year." Pediatric resident Chantel Walker was named
"Pediatric Resident of the Year."

Compiled by Charlie Patton

